WEBVTT

00:00.875 --> 00:04.173
Hot in Cleveland is recored in
front of a live studio audience.

00:04.328 --> 00:06.774
Did you know Cleveland
was originally spelled...

00:06.830 --> 00:09.860
c-l-e-a-v-e-l-a-n-d?

00:09.940 --> 00:11.496
From John Moses cleaveland,

00:11.528 --> 00:13.438
- see, their dropped the 'a'...!
- Shut up!

00:14.199 --> 00:17.621
Thank you.

00:17.654 --> 00:19.149
The nominations for
the daytime emmys...

00:19.183 --> 00:20.312
- were just announced.
- Oh.

00:20.346 --> 00:23.469
All right, who cares,
who cares, ah--

00:23.503 --> 00:25.894
best actress.
Susan lucci...

00:25.929 --> 00:29.349
Well-deserved.

00:29.384 --> 00:32.772
Crystal mcallister,
nobody, nobody, and...

00:32.807 --> 00:33.935
Victoria Chase!

00:33.969 --> 00:36.327
Yay!
Good for you.

00:36.362 --> 00:38.421
Oh, it's my 16th nomination.
Uh, waiter?

00:38.455 --> 00:41.112
Uh, I realize it's only
8:00 in the morning,

00:41.147 --> 00:42.839
but we're celebrating,
and I would like...

00:42.874 --> 00:44.900
some champagne
in my orange juice.

00:44.934 --> 00:48.089
You mean the usual?

00:48.124 --> 00:50.714
Yes.

00:50.749 --> 00:53.506
Although I've never won
this thing.

00:53.539 --> 00:56.330
And this year, I definitely
don't have a chance.

00:56.365 --> 00:58.989
<i>Crystal mcallister from
the strong and the gorgeous...</i>

00:59.022 --> 01:01.380
pulled a really underhanded
stunt.

01:01.414 --> 01:02.609
What'd she do?

01:02.644 --> 01:05.500
She died.

01:05.535 --> 01:07.593
Aka award magnet.

01:07.628 --> 01:09.853
You know I can't compete
with death.

01:11.216 --> 01:13.475
Oh, it's my son.

01:13.509 --> 01:14.771
He's driving back to college
from L.A.

01:14.805 --> 01:16.465
And I begged him to stop here
on the way.

01:16.500 --> 01:17.728
So he's gonna be here
this afternoon.

01:17.763 --> 01:19.290
Well, how's he doing?

01:19.324 --> 01:21.715
You know, I don't know.
He rarely speaks to me.

01:21.750 --> 01:23.609
I get the occasional grunt
on mother's day.

01:23.644 --> 01:26.134
Oh, kids can be
so ungrateful.

01:26.168 --> 01:28.493
I mean, you get them
the best nannies money can buy...

01:28.527 --> 01:30.022
and then they blackmail you
with threats...

01:30.056 --> 01:33.877
<i>to write a mommie dearest.</i>

01:33.911 --> 01:37.265
Oh, look who's back
from Hollywood.

01:37.299 --> 01:39.359
What was it like
doing Brad pitt's eyebrows?

01:39.393 --> 01:42.349
Does he smell like
fresh cream...

01:42.383 --> 01:44.874
on a fine spring morning?

01:44.908 --> 01:48.895
'Cause that's how
I imagine it.

01:48.929 --> 01:51.054
Elka, celebrities
are just like everyone else.

01:51.088 --> 01:53.547
You take that back.

01:53.581 --> 01:55.108
Oh, I'm just
starting to wonder...

01:55.142 --> 01:56.304
if there isn't more to life...

01:56.338 --> 01:58.631
than removing celebrities'
unwanted hair.

01:58.664 --> 02:01.055
I think I'm having
a mid-life crisis.

02:01.090 --> 02:05.243
Mid-life?

02:05.277 --> 02:07.768
You know, if you really are
having a crisis,

02:07.802 --> 02:09.097
maybe you should see
a therapist.

02:09.131 --> 02:11.721
The only therapy I need
is liquid therapy.

02:11.756 --> 02:14.945
Hello.

02:14.979 --> 02:16.606
Victoria got another
emmy nomination.

02:16.640 --> 02:17.769
Congratulations.

02:17.803 --> 02:19.198
She can't win.

02:19.232 --> 02:23.052
She's up against a dead girl.

02:23.087 --> 02:25.344
You didn't have
Susan Lucci killed, did you?

02:25.379 --> 02:28.734
No. That was just trash talk.

02:31.042 --> 02:38.485
Sync by mczolly
www.addic7ed.com

02:38.913 --> 02:42.253
the oddest thing
just happened.

02:42.288 --> 02:45.361
My Agent says that
there's this huge Internet rumor...

02:45.395 --> 02:48.369
that I'm dying from
some disease called...

02:48.403 --> 02:50.841
Well, I can't even remember
the name.

02:50.875 --> 02:53.346
Flett-giordano syndrome.

02:53.381 --> 02:54.616
And you're welcome.

02:54.650 --> 02:57.556
What?
You started the rumor?

02:57.591 --> 02:59.093
Well, now you can beat
the dead girl...

02:59.128 --> 03:00.931
at her own game.

03:00.966 --> 03:02.235
But--

03:02.269 --> 03:04.640
but you can't just say that
I have a disease.

03:04.674 --> 03:06.245
I've never even heard of it.

03:06.279 --> 03:09.051
Well, no one has.
That's the beauty of it.

03:10.990 --> 03:13.194
Uh, Victoria Chase.

03:13.228 --> 03:17.104
<i>Yes, I'll hold for
people magazine.</i>

03:18.241 --> 03:19.376
Elka.

03:19.411 --> 03:21.849
I need a list
of really fun things...

03:21.883 --> 03:23.151
to do in Cleveland.

03:23.186 --> 03:25.156
Will's coming,
and we haven't really...

03:25.191 --> 03:26.426
spoken much since
the divorce,

03:26.461 --> 03:27.931
and I really wanna
reconnect with him.

03:27.965 --> 03:29.968
So if you were
a 20-year-old boy,

03:30.002 --> 03:33.209
what would you wanna do
with your mom?

03:33.244 --> 03:37.286
Watch her buy me beer?

03:37.321 --> 03:40.127
Hey, joy.
Where you been?

03:40.161 --> 03:42.131
Okay, don't go all Melanie
on me,

03:42.165 --> 03:43.935
but I decided to take
your suggestion...

03:43.970 --> 03:46.675
and I met with a couple
of potential therapists.

03:46.710 --> 03:49.182
Wow. How did it go?

03:49.216 --> 03:50.885
They're all so nosy.

03:50.919 --> 03:52.489
Asking me questions about...

03:52.524 --> 03:55.597
my childhood
and feelings and sex...

03:55.632 --> 03:57.535
and saying I need to come in
four times a week.

03:57.569 --> 04:00.508
I mean, who can talk about
themselves for that long?

04:00.543 --> 04:03.616
And then at age 12,
I decided becoming an actress...

04:03.651 --> 04:06.557
would be the best way
to serve humanity.

04:06.591 --> 04:08.027
<i>No, no, no, thank you.</i>

04:08.061 --> 04:10.232
Oh, Elka.

04:10.266 --> 04:12.571
You are a genius.

04:12.605 --> 04:14.409
Elka came up with
this Internet rumor...

04:14.443 --> 04:17.450
that I have this very,
very promotable deadly disease.

04:17.483 --> 04:21.226
Well, I'm sure nothing could
go wrong with that.

04:21.260 --> 04:24.634
Oh.
It's a text from my Agent.

04:24.668 --> 04:28.644
<i>Entertainment weekly
and in style magazine...</i>

04:28.678 --> 04:30.046
both want me.

04:30.081 --> 04:32.385
Oh, and, and also,

04:32.419 --> 04:34.858
the flett-giordano
syndrome foundation...

04:34.892 --> 04:36.463
want to come
and meet with me here.

04:36.497 --> 04:39.436
Oh, well, this will just
legitimize the hell out of it.

04:40.874 --> 04:42.811
What kind of disease
is it?

04:42.846 --> 04:45.617
I-I don't know.
Elka?

04:45.652 --> 04:46.954
You know, I'm,
I'm happy to lie to win,

04:46.988 --> 04:49.427
but I-I don't wanna
lose my hair or anything.

04:49.461 --> 04:52.367
- The only symptom is fatigue.
- That's perfect.

04:52.402 --> 04:54.239
I mean, I can play tired
in my sleep.

04:56.177 --> 04:58.816
Ah, luckily, this disease
hasn't affected my wit.

05:00.254 --> 05:03.627
Oh, that's will.
My baby's here.

05:03.662 --> 05:05.332
Hi, honey!

05:05.366 --> 05:07.970
- Hi, just a sec.
- Okay.

05:08.005 --> 05:11.212
It's good to see you.

05:15.690 --> 05:17.894
- Good to see you, sweetie.
- Yeah.

05:17.929 --> 05:19.666
The facial hair
makes you look a little...

05:19.700 --> 05:22.005
Foreign, but cute.

05:22.040 --> 05:23.141
Come on in.

05:23.175 --> 05:24.478
You know joy and Victoria.

05:24.512 --> 05:26.182
- Both: Hey, will.
- Hi.

05:26.217 --> 05:27.351
Ah, this is Elka Ostrovsky.

05:27.386 --> 05:29.289
Nice to meet you, will.

05:29.324 --> 05:30.526
Nice to meet you too.

05:30.560 --> 05:32.798
Well, your mom picks up
and moves to Cleveland.

05:32.832 --> 05:34.268
You must have
a million questions.

05:34.302 --> 05:36.808
No, I'm good.

05:36.842 --> 05:38.145
I fixed up the guest room
for you,

05:38.179 --> 05:39.782
but I thought maybe
we'd go out to lunch first.

05:39.816 --> 05:41.787
I kinda just wanna crash,
if that's cool.

05:41.821 --> 05:45.161
Sure. Sure.
It's cool. Very cool.

05:45.195 --> 05:46.497
Do you want me to show you
where the room is?

05:46.532 --> 05:48.636
- I'll find it.
- Yeah. You can find it.

05:48.670 --> 05:50.174
You're good like that.

05:50.208 --> 05:51.677
He can find it.

05:51.711 --> 05:53.146
I hope it's your daughter...

05:53.182 --> 05:56.789
who's gonna decide
which home to put you in.

06:01.802 --> 06:04.341
Well, this is fun.
The two of us.

06:04.375 --> 06:06.613
Getting a chance to talk
and catch up...

06:06.647 --> 06:10.388
and shoot the breeze.

06:12.361 --> 06:14.030
So how's school?

06:14.065 --> 06:16.804
- Good.
- Oh. Yeah?

06:17.941 --> 06:20.312
Well, you certainly have
a lot to say...

06:20.347 --> 06:23.019
To someone.

06:23.053 --> 06:24.689
- What?
- Nothing.

06:24.724 --> 06:27.028
You know.
I text. So I get it.

06:27.062 --> 06:28.399
Sorry,
what did you say, mom?

06:28.433 --> 06:31.974
You know, lol.
Omg.

06:32.009 --> 06:35.516
Om--
you know what--g.

06:35.551 --> 06:38.055
You know it's not cursing
if you say a letter, mom.

06:38.089 --> 06:39.626
Oh, sure. Sure.

06:39.661 --> 06:41.998
"F."
"F!"...

06:45.107 --> 06:47.645
You know, honey.

06:47.680 --> 06:49.684
We never got a chance
to talk about the divorce.

06:49.718 --> 06:51.956
And we can do that,
if you'd like.

06:51.990 --> 06:53.659
No, I get it.

06:53.694 --> 06:56.299
Stuff happens.
I'm good.

06:56.334 --> 06:59.207
Okay.

